Media player

Guernsey updates on coronavirus: 23-27 March

23 March 202023 March 2020

And we'll keep you signed in.

Sign in or Register

Why sign in to the BBC?

Got a TV Licence?

You need one to watch live TV on any channel or device, and BBC programmes on iPlayer. Its the law.

Find out more
I dont have a TV Licence.

Summary

  1. Updates for 23-27 March. Our live coverage continues on Monday
  2. Guernsey residents told to 'stay at home'
  3. Non-essential shops and community spaces closed
  4. All public gatherings of more than two people banned
  5. Thirty-six confirmed cases from more than 500 test results
  6. Anyone with clinical questions can call 01481 756938 or 756969 between 08:00-22:00 daily
  7. Latest advice from the States is available at gov.gg/coronavirus
